bigail Hooker 00099","notes":"One of the three Hart-Hooker marriages between 1719 and 1726: three sons of Capt. John Hart (X00033) married three daughters of Hon. John Hooker (H00030). Lieut. Samuel Hart married I00029's wife's sister Abigail Hooker (H00099, b.~1697); she had married Nathaniel Hart in 1719."},{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00101","display_label":"Sister-in-law via Hart-Hooker triple marriage, 1719-1726","link_text":"Sarah Hooker 00101","notes":"One of the three Hart-Hooker marriages between 1719 and 1726: three sons of Capt. John Hart (X00033) married three daughters of Hon. John Hooker (H00030). Lieut. Samuel Hart married I00029's wife's sister Sarah Hooker (H00101, b.~1701); she had married Matthew Hart in 1726."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Three Hart brothers each married a Hooker sister","body":"He was one of three sons of Capt. John Hart who each married a daughter of John Hooker Esq. of Farmington — Nathaniel married Abigail, Samuel married Mary, and Matthew married Sarah, between 1719 and 1725, binding two of Farmington's founding families."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Died when his only son was fourteen","body":"Lieut. Samuel Hart had planned a collegiate education for his only son Samuel, but died when the boy was about fourteen. His widow, unwilling to part with him, kept him home and provided the best education locally available."}],"baptism":{"year":1692,"month":9,"day":18,"city":"Farmington","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"bio":{"title":"Lieutenant","display_name":"Lieut. Samuel Hart","first_name":"Samuel","last_name":"Hart","married_names":[]},"landmarks":[],"residence":{"city":"Berlin","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"samuel-hart-1692"},"H00100":{"id":"H00100","has_descendants_documente